<tr class="bugnote" id="c1393">
        <td class="bugnote-public">
				<span class="small">(<a href="view3684.html?id=599#c1393" title="Direct link to note">0001393)</a></span><br />
		<a href="view_user_page3ebc.html?id=64">somzzz</a>		<span class="small">(developer)</span>
				<br />
		<span class="small">2014-03-13 00:22</span><br />
				<br /><div class="small">
				</div>
	</td>
	<td class="bugnote-note-public">
		Discovered and fixed the following bug:<br />
Navigating away from the Administration tab saves the currently opened page (example: &quot;Administration/0&quot; or &quot;Administration/1/889/All_Tabs&quot;), but returing to it does not properly configure the navigation panel if the page you left is a Administration/Tab/Subtab. Unlike the usual behaviour for a tab/subtab, when the navigation panel shows a label without hyperlink, it now shows a clickable hyperlink. Clicking it opens the list of models. <br />
<br />
This behaviour is not natural for the existing code and is caused by an untreated case and a dependency between the loading of distinct visual content (the panel and the main view) and the present navigation chain.<br />
<br />
Details about how this bug was fixed and integrated in the patch for issue 599 are provided in the readme file attached to the patch submission.<br />
<br />
Steps to reproduce ( for revision 1559 ):<br />
- open Administration/2/pick_a_project or Administration/3/pick_an_organization<br />
- return to the dashboard without closing Administration<br />
- return to the opened Administration tab<br />
- the entire navigation panel is clickable<br />
- click Administration/2 or Administration/3, return to the lists of models	</td>
</tr>
